main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects (UFOs) were observed over Tucson, Arizona, on September 8 and 9, 1960.
interesting points: The first sighting involved an object moving rapidly in a northeasterly direction with a bright white light,The object was under observation for approximately 2 minutes before disappearing,During a radar observation on June 8, 1952, 20 objects were detected moving rapidly,The UFOs were noted to have no navigation lights and appeared metallic,One report described a cylindrical glowing orange UFO in the Caribbean Sea observed by a crew in a U.S. Orion Clipper.
sighted object: multiple unidentified flying objects with varying shapes and behaviors
witness description: a private citizen with no special training in aircraft identification
